<div style="padding: 0 10px;">
<h2>Plastic Recycling Program</h2>
In an effort to reduce the number of plastic containers that end up in the city landfill, Specified Technical Sales Ltd. &amp; GE Water &amp; Process Technologies have teamed up to organize a recycling program for their customers in the Calgary area.

We can arrange to pick up your clean, empty plastic containers, OR you can drop them off at our receiving department: #214, 3750 46 Ave SE, Calgary AB, T2B 0L1 during our regular business hours Monday to Friday 8 am to 4 pm.

Arrangements can be made for a courier to pick up plastics, from your business, for a nominal fee of approximately $35.00, within Calgary city limits. Maximum # of pails, per pick up, is currently, limited to 60 pails or 12 drums.

&nbsp;
<h2>Glycol Recycling Program</h2>
In an effort to reduce the discharge of glycols to the sewer system, Specified Technical Sales Ltd. has teamed up with a local recycler to remove and recycle ethylene and propylene glycols for re-use in other industries.

We can arrange bulk removal or can accept drums containers, at our Calgary receiving department: #214, 3750 46 Ave SE, Calgary AB, T2B 0L1 during our regular business hours Monday to Friday 8 am to 4 pm.

Arrangements must be made in advance and minimal charges may apply for this service.

[imageframe lightbox="no" style_type="none" bordercolor="" bordersize="0px" stylecolor="" align="none" animation_type="0" animation_direction="down" animation_speed="0.1" class="" id=""]<img src="http://specified.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/recycle.png" alt="Recycle" />[/imageframe]
<h3>who to contact</h3>
Crystalle Holtz - Specified Technical Sales

(403)253-2881

&nbsp;
<h2>Plastic Items Accepted for Recycling</h2>
<ul>
	<li>250ml Sample Bottles</li>
	<li>250ml, 500ml, 1L &amp; 4L reagent bottles</li>
	<li>20L pails &amp; 205L drums</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;
<h2>How to Prepare Plastics</h2>
<ul>
	<li>Plastics must be empty, lids removed, triple rinsed &amp; pails stacked one inside another</li>
</ul>
</div>
